    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Heavy clouds loom overhead and a mist-like rain drizzles down, covering your cloak in a spider web of beaded droplets. The water clings to Sirin's helm like a veneer of diamond, somehow catching and reflecting light in the gloom. The Archon of Song treads the damp road with chin raised, imperiously scowling down her nose at the weather.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>Just off the road ahead you spy a gathering of tents and canopies, a small settlement of the itinerant, bearing no banners or heraldry. Sirin pauses, the specter of a grin tugging at the corners of her mouth.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>Approach the camp.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>Ask Sirin if she knows what's going on.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Tiersmen have cleared the tall grass from small areas to either side of the road. While there are a few true tents, most of the shelters are large canvas tarps suspended from poles or tied off to trees. Bedrolls litter the damp ground, though a few of the larger canopies boast a hammock or two.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>She smiles. "I would hardly want to ruin the surprise, Fatebinder."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Force the issue.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Archon scowls as you demand an answer from her. "I'm not entirely certain. But they feel familiar. I feel... my music in them." She crosses her arms. "You could always go over there and ask them who they are."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Send Sirin in first.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>You demand that Sirin precede you into the encampment.

"What?" she asks. "Don't tell me you're afraid of a handful of dirty peasants in the rain!" She shakes her head. "You're VERY impressive, Archon."

She pivots on her heel and walks towards the tents.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Men and women in rough-spun tunics and woolen cloaks cluster around fires, seeking warmth against the weather. Few look up at your arrival, though those who do immediately come to their feet.

"Archon!" one gasps.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bask in their adulation.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>Demand their obeisance.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>Demand tribute.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>[10000 rings.] Provide money.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>Ignore them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>You raise your arms to either side, palms open and turned upward as if to catch the rain, and welcome the attention of these peons.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>You square your shoulders and straighten your back, demanding that these peons show you the courtesies proper for your station.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>You open a bag, drop it beside the road, and demand a tithe of whatever goods these peons possess. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>You untie several rings from your belt and toss them among the peasants. You're surprised when they don't immediately grasp for them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>You decide to give the peasants no mind, determined to instead press on.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>All around you, Tiersmen rise to their feet. Their murmuring rises, a quiet chorus.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>One of the older peasants blinks at you. "Sorry... who are you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>Almost as one, the peasants drop to their knees in the wet grass, bowing low and chanting a single name: "Sirin."

Sirin smiles so sweetly it's saccharine. "My adoring public."
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Demand Sirin explain.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>Break up the camp.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>Enslave the camp.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>Conscript the camp.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>Recruit the camp.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>Leave.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>She gestures to the gathered throng. "They seem to be peasants paying proper respect to their betters. I understand why you would fail to recognize such a thing."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>Accept her explanation.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>Require clarification.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>You nod and turn your attention back to the peasants.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>She huffs when you demand further explanation. "When I abandoned [url=glossary:lethian's crossing]Lethian's Crossing[/url], I left these wondrous folk behind. It seems they've come looking for me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>Send peasants home.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>Tell Sirin to deal with them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Tiersmen look to one another as you demand they return to the Crossing. A stout woman with deeply-lined features clears her throat. "Begging your pardon, Archon, but we've been searching for the Archon of Song for some time. Now that we found her, we can't just leave her!" A general furor of agreement rises from the group.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Archon's voice rises and the air seems to lighten, its weight lifting from your back. Their eyes widening, the Tiersmen fall to their knees, attention entirely rapt.

A soft fogginess settles in your mind.

Sirin turns to you, her large blue eyes filling your vision.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Are you sure I can't keep them?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>You inform the peasants of their new role in service to the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] Legion and direct them to Iron Hearth.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>You inform the peasants that they're now members of the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url]... or rather, those who survive will be. Sirin glares hatefully at you as you send her former followers to Cacophony and the waiting Archon of Secrets.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>You offer the Tiersmen roles among your coalition, and they happily accept, grateful for the opportunity to live in proximity to their beloved Archon of Song.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm sure."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Send them to the Citadel, then."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Glare silently.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>You continue your journey through Haven only to find that your small party has gained a following of fifty peasants. They trail behind you, a slow, attention-grabbing column.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>Leave.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>You continue your journey through Haven only to find that your small party has gained a following of fifty peasants. They trail behind you, a slow, attention-grabbing column.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>Start killing them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>Citing your authority as a Fatebinder and Archon, you order the camp struck. The peasants eagerly attend to your ultimatum, pulling up stakes and rolling up beds.
 
You turn to leave, pleasantly surprised by how tractable these Tiersmen turned out. You continue down the road, but soon realize that the peasants are following behind you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>Your dagger opens the woman's throat in a flash of blood. As she falls, you gut the next nearest peasant. The people back away from you as one, and you again demand that they return to the crossing.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>They look to the Archon of Song for support, but when Sirin only glares at you, the peasants begin to break up, gathering their belongings for the return to the Crossing.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>They look to the Archon of Song, and one of their number shouts, "We'll happily die for the Songbird!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>Kill them all.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>You move to drive your blade into another peasant's stomach, when Sirin puts a hand on yours. "Please, let me..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>Tell Sirin to deal with them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>It's long, bloody work, and more of the Tiersmen flee then fall beneath your wrath, but you've soon cleared the camp of Sirin-worshipers and scattered them to the wilds.

You turn from the corpses and continue towards your destination.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>Having bound their fates, you continue your journey.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fine!" The word cuts through the warmth in your mind like a chilled sickle, and for a moment, the eyes of the peasants narrow upon you. Then Sirin's song continues, the Tiersmen's features go slack, and the Archon of Song directs them towards their new destination.

"There," she hisses. "Done."

You continue on your journey.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
